that there's too many rules

00:02:13.520 --> 00:02:14.585 align:middle line:10%
and regulations there.

00:02:14.585 --> 00:02:14.840 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:02:14.840 --> 00:02:15.830 align:middle line:90%
Big difference.

00:02:15.830 --> 00:02:16.400 align:middle line:90%
>>ANTHONY: Quite a bit.

00:02:16.400 --> 00:02:18.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did your
parents encourage you

00:02:18.140 --> 00:02:20.700 align:middle line:90%
to get into the psychic world?

00:02:20.700 --> 00:02:25.040 align:middle line:84%
>>ANTHONY: Actually, it
was such a fact of life--

00:02:25.040 --> 00:02:27.860 align:middle line:84%
when I was a child, they
wanted me to keep it quiet.

00:02:27.860 --> 00:02:29.810 align:middle line:84%
And they said, you can
talk about it to us,

00:02:29.810 --> 00:02:32.530 align:middle line:84%
but people outside of the
family won't understand.

00:02:32.530 --> 00:02:34.780 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Or they'll think
you're strange or something.

00:02:34.780 --> 00:02:35.630 align:middle line:90%
>>ANTHONY: Yeah.

00:02:35.630 --> 00:02:37.130 align:middle line:90%
They think that you're strange.

00:02:37.130 --> 00:02:39.740 align:middle line:84%
And my father's
sister, Marjorie,

00:02:39.740 --> 00:02:42.170 align:middle line:84%
was an extremely
gifted psychic medium.

00:02:42.170 --> 00:02:46.130 align:middle line:84%
And the problem is her husband,
who was very religious,

00:02:46.130 --> 00:02:48.170 align:middle line:84%
felt that she was doing
the work of Satan.

00:02:48.170 --> 00:02:51.020 align:middle line:84%
And what would happen,
or what happened,

00:02:51.020 --> 00:02:53.930 align:middle line:84%
is she warned him about
going to work one day.

00:02:53.930 --> 00:02:56.870 align:middle line:84%
And he worked at a steel
plant in Pennsylvania.

00:02:56.870 --> 00:02:58.190 align:middle line:90%
And she didn't want him to go.

00:02:58.190 --> 00:02:59.898 align:middle line:84%
And he worked in this
machine shop there.

00:02:59.898 --> 00:03:03.050 align:middle line:84%
Well, that day,
George, a crane was

00:03:03.050 --> 00:03:05.300 align:middle line:84%
lifting thousands of
pounds of steel beams,

00:03:05.300 --> 00:03:08.720 align:middle line:84%
and the cable snapped, and it
flattened the machine shop,

00:03:08.720 --> 00:03:09.860 align:middle line:90%
killing everybody there.

00:03:09.860 --> 00:03:11.500 align:middle line:90%
So he would have been there.

00:03:11.500 --> 00:03:13.250 align:middle line:84%
And you think he would
have been grateful.

00:03:13.250 --> 00:03:16.250 align:middle line:84%
But instead, he felt that
she was doing evil work,

00:03:16.250 --> 00:03:18.810 align:middle line:84%
and he had her
involuntarily committed.

00:03:18.810 --> 00:03:19.610 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:03:19.610 --> 00:03:20.410 align:middle line:90%
>>ANTHONY: Yeah.

00:03:20.410 --> 00:03:22.940 align:middle line:84%
And they subjected her
to electroshock therapy

00:03:22.940 --> 00:03:24.680 align:middle line:90%
for over four months.

00:03:24.680 --> 00:03:25.490 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Jeez.

00:03:25.490 --> 00:03:26.450 align:middle line:90%
That was cruel.

00:03:26.450 --> 00:03:29.720 align:middle line:84%
>>ANTHONY: Yeah, until she
never saw spirits again.

00:03:29.720 --> 00:03:31.197 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They
forced her to stop.

00:03:31.197 --> 00:03:32.780 align:middle line:84%
>>ANTHONY: They
forced her to do this.

00:03:32.780 --> 00:03:35.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's how it was
looked at in those days.

00:03:35.900 --> 00:03:38.970 align:middle line:84%
So psychics and mediums have
been persecuted for centuries.

00:03:38.970 --> 00:03:41.000 align:middle line:84%
And so when I was a
little kid, my dad

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:42.980 align:middle line:84%
didn't want that
happening to me.

00:03:42.980 --> 00:03:44.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Right, and it
probably would have.

00:03:44.930 --> 00:03:46.310 align:middle line:90%
>>ANTHONY: It could have.

00:03:46.310 --> 00:03:48.380 align:middle line:90%
Now, it's openly discussed.

00:03:48.380 --> 00:03:50.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You are no
longer a trial lawyer.

00:03:50.180 --> 00:03:52.370 align:middle line:84%
You decided to devote
your entire career

00:03:52.370 --> 00:03:53.750 align:middle line:90%
to the psychic realm.

00:03:53.750 --> 00:03:57.500 align:middle line:84%
But when you were, did you
use these psychic abilities

00:03:57.500 --> 00:03:59.300 align:middle line:90%
in any of your cases?

00:03:59.300 --> 00:04:01.730 align:middle line:84%
>>ANTHONY: It's part of
my skill set and who I am,

00:04:01.730 --> 00:04:03.830 align:middle line:84%
so it certainly did
come up, particularly

00:04:03.830 --> 00:04:08.570 align:middle line:84%
during jury selection, which is
the segment before we actually

00:04:08.570 --> 00:04:10.440 align:middle line:84%
begin putting
witnesses on the stand.

00:04:10.440 --> 00:04:10.740 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:04:10.740 --> 00:04:12.448 align:middle line:84%
>>ANTHONY: Both the
prosecution, defense,

00:04:12.448 --> 00:04:13.940 align:middle line:84%
or the plaintiff
and the defense,

00:04:13.940 --> 00:04:16.250 align:middle line:84%
get to ask the prospective
jurors questions

00:04:16.250 --> 00:04:18.649 align:middle line:84%
so we can narrow
down to make sure we

00:04:18.649 --> 00:04:20.120 align:middle line:90%
have a fair and impartial jury.

00:04:20.120 --> 00:04:24.057 align:middle line:84%
And that's where it really
started becoming very useful.

00:04:24.057 --> 00:04:25.640 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So what
does a psychic lawyer

00:04:25.640 --> 00:04:27.880 align:middle line:90%
think about consciousness?

00:04:27.880 --> 00:04:31.990 align:middle line:84%
>>ANTHONY: Consciousness is the
energy of who and what we are.

00:04:31.990 --> 00:04:36.430 align:middle line:84%
In spiritual circles,
but in people of faith,

00:04:36.430 --> 00:04:39.040 align:middle line:84%
it's called the
soul or the spirit.

00:04:39.040 --> 00:04:42.220 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness is used by
philosophers, psychologists,

00:04:42.220 --> 00:04:43.510 align:middle line:90%
and scientists.

00:04:43.510 --> 00:04:45.580 align:middle line:84%
And that's the essence
of who we are--

00:04:45.580 --> 00:04:49.450 align:middle line:84%
our personality, individuality,
our likes, dislikes,

00:04:49.450 --> 00:04:51.070 align:middle line:90%
our observations.

00:04:51.070 --> 00:04:52.750 align:middle line:90%
And consciousness is eternal.

00:04:52.750 --> 00:04:54.130 align:middle line:90%
It's pure energy.

00:04:54.130 --> 00:04:56.950 align:middle line:84%
And what's fascinating,
George, about consciousness,

00:04:56.950 --> 00:04:59.860 align:middle line:84%
is that it is
capable of perception

00:04:59.860 --> 00:05:03.140 align:middle line:84%
beyond our five physical senses
of sight, hearing, taste,

00:05:03.140 --> 00:05:04.360 align:middle line:90%
smell, and touch.

00:05:04.360 --> 00:05:07.510 align:middle line:84%
Our consciousness is also
capable of perceiving

00:05:07.510 --> 00:05:10.690 align:middle line:84%
dimensions beyond our
physical material world.

00:05:10.690 --> 00:05:14.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why isn't science
dabbling with this?

00:05:14.080 --> 00:05:17.290 align:middle line:84%
>>ANTHONY: The interesting
thing is that neuroscience

00:05:17.290 --> 00:05:19.270 align:middle line:90%
is the study of the brain.

00:05:19.270 --> 00:05:22.540 align:middle line:84%
And the official position
of neuroscience, George,

00:05:22.540 --> 00:05:25.330 align:middle line:84%
is that consciousness
is created by chemical

00:05:25.330 --> 00:05:28.600 align:middle line:84%
reactions and electrical
impulses within the brain.

00:05:28.600 --> 00:05:31.580 align:middle line:84%
But they're completely at
a loss how to explain why.

00:05:31.580 --> 00:05:33.970 align:middle line:84%
In fact, if you read
a neuroscience book,

00:05:33.970 --> 00:05:36.130 align:middle line:84%
there will be 900
pages on functions

00:05:36.130 --> 00:05:38.800 align:middle line:84%
of the brain and maybe
two or three paragraphs

00:05:38.800 --> 00:05:40.630 align:middle line:90%
about consciousness.

00:05:40.630 --> 00:05:43.750 align:middle line:84%
And we have to instead
look at the brain

00:05:43.750 --> 00:05:46.720 align:middle line:84%
as what it is-- a
carbon-12 and salt

00:05:46.720 --> 00:05:48.790 align:middle line:90%
resonator floating in water.

00:05:48.790 --> 00:05:50.530 align:middle line:84%
So it's like a
computer hard drive.

00:05:50.530 --> 00:05:53.200 align:middle line:84%
And a hard drive on a computer
doesn't create the programs

00:05:53.200 --> 00:05:56.110 align:middle line:84%
on it or the data,
it merely hosts them.

00:05:56.110 --> 00:05:58.990 align:middle line:84%
And I believe it's the
same with our brain.

00:05:58.990 --> 00:06:01.060 align:middle line:84%
It does not create
consciousness,

00:06:01.060 --> 00:06:02.620 align:middle line:90%
it merely hosts it.

00:06:02.620 --> 00:06:05.840 align:middle line:84%
The consciousness pre-exist the
brain, comes into the brain.

00:06:05.840 --> 00:06:08.050 align:middle line:84%
And when the hard
drive brain crashes--

00:06:08.050 --> 00:06:09.460 align:middle line:90%
in other words, when we die--

00:06:09.460 --> 00:06:12.220 align:middle line:84%
it gets uploaded to
a higher frequency.

00:06:12.220 --> 00:06:14.110 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: As long as we
keep getting uploaded,

00:06:14.110 --> 00:06:15.122 align:middle line:90%
that's all that matters.

00:06:15.122 --> 00:06:17.080 align:middle line:84%
>>ANTHONY: As long as we
keep getting uploaded.

00:06:17.080 --> 00:06:19.450 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is
quantum paradigm?

00:06:19.450 --> 00:06:23.650 align:middle line:84%
>>ANTHONY: Quantum, well, first
off, with quantum physics,

00:06:23.650 --> 00:06:26.730 align:middle line:84%
people like to throw the
word around as a buzz phrase.

00:06:26.730 --> 00:06:27.730 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Tough word too.

00:06:27.730 --> 00:06:28.530 align:middle line:90%
>>ANTHONY: Yeah.

00:06:28.530 --> 00:06:30.520 align:middle line:84%
And we know from
science that everything

00:06:30.520 --> 00:06:32.050 align:middle line:84%
is made of molecules,
which are made

00:06:32.050 --> 00:06:34.330 align:middle line:84%
of atoms, which are made
of electrons, protons,

00:06:34.330 --> 00:06:35.440 align:middle line:90%
and neutrons.

00:06:35.440 --> 00:06:39.700 align:middle line:84%
But on the most basic,
level everything

00:06:39.700 --> 00:06:44.200 align:middle line:84%
is composed of quanta, which
is pure electromagnetic energy.

00:06:44.200 --> 00:06:47.410 align:middle line:84%
So the most fundamental
building block of everything

00:06:47.410 --> 00:06:50.020 align:middle line:84%
in existence-- and that's you,
me, the air we're breathing,

00:06:50.020 --> 00:06:54.170 align:middle line:84%
the light, our planet, the
nuclear reactions in the sun--

00:06:54.170 --> 00:06:54.970 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:06:54.970 --> 00:06:59.020 align:middle line:84%
>>ANTHONY: --everything
is electromagnetic energy.

00:06:59.020 --> 00:07:04.960 align:middle line:84%
And the quantum paradigm is that
we can leap from one dimension

00:07:04.960 --> 00:07:05.890 align:middle line:90%
to another.

00:07:05.890 --> 00:07:06.910 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Instantly.

00:07:06.910 --> 00:07:07.840 align:middle line:90%
>>ANTHONY: Instantly.

00:07:07.840 --> 00:07:10.090 align:middle line:84%
You know, George, we all
have days where we don't feel

00:07:10.090 --> 00:07:13.330 align:middle line:84%
like we're all here, and
that's because we're not.

00:07:13.330 --> 00:07:16.300 align:middle line:84%
And if we look at the
Schwarzschild quantum lattice

00:07:16.300 --> 00:07:20.260 align:middle line:84%
theory-- back in the early 20th
century, Karl Schwarzschild,

00:07:20.260 --> 00:07:22.670 align:middle line:84%
good friend of Max Planck
and Albert Einstein--

00:07:22.670 --> 00:07:23.470 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:07:23.470 --> 00:07:26.200 align:middle line:84%
>>ANTHONY: He theorized that
electrons would disappear

00:07:26.200 --> 00:07:28.180 align:middle line:84%
from one location,
appear in another,

00:07:28.180 --> 00:07:30.550 align:middle line:84%
without traversing
the matter in between.

00:07:30.550 --> 00:07:33.220 align:middle line:84%
Now this has been
recreated in laboratories.

00:07:33.220 --> 00:07:36.220 align:middle line:84%
So subatomic
particles are quantum

00:07:36.220 --> 00:07:38.430 align:middle line:84%
leaping to another
dimension all the time.

00:07:38.430 --> 00:07:39.430 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's amazing.

00:07:39.430 --> 00:07:40.388 align:middle line:90%
>>ANTHONY: Well, it is.

00:07:40.388 --> 00:07:44.050 align:middle line:84%
And if you take the energy
that's in our brain, our soul,

00:07:44.050 --> 00:07:46.930 align:middle line:84%
particles of that-- because
it's electromagnetic energy--

00:07:46.930 --> 00:07:49.600 align:middle line:84%
are quantum leaping to
this other dimension.

00:07:49.600 --> 00:07:54.220 align:middle line:84%
And now, George, we know
from quantum entanglement

00:07:54.220 --> 00:07:57.400 align:middle line:84%
that when two subatomic
particles go apart,

00:07:57.400 --> 00:07:59.380 align:middle line:84%
they remain
connected, entangled.

00:07:59.380 --> 00:08:01.000 align:middle line:84%
And something that
happens to one

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:02.840 align:middle line:84%
immediately happens
to the other,

00:08:02.840 --> 00:08:07.250 align:middle line:84%
even if, as scientists theorize,
they're a billion miles apart.

00:08:07.250 --> 00:08:08.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That is dramatic.

00:08:08.590 --> 00:08:11.320 align:middle line:84%
On the "Mystery
Teachings" Gaia show,

00:08:11.320 --> 00:08:15.798 align:middle line:84%
physicist Dr. Theresa Bullard
talks about this paradigm.

00:08:15.798 --> 00:08:18.340 align:middle line:84%
>>THERESA BULLARD: Let's take
a look at these two paradigms--

00:08:18.340 --> 00:08:22.360 align:middle line:84%
Newtonian versus quantum--
and how they differ.

00:08:22.360 --> 00:08:25.450 align:middle line:84%
The Newtonian paradigm
is based upon the ideas

00:08:25.450 --> 00:08:30.820 align:middle line:84%
of determinism, separatism,
reductionism, and materialism.

00:08:30.820 --> 00:08:33.460 align:middle line:10%
In essence, this
says that everything

00:08:33.460 --> 00:08:38.289 align:middle line:10%
can be isolated and reduced
to its individual parts, which

00:08:38.289 --> 00:08:42.520 align:middle line:10%
must function in a linear,
logical, clockwork way.

00:08:42.520 --> 00:08:46.180 align:middle line:10%
It says that things should be
predictable and controllable.

00:08:46.180 --> 00:08:49.660 align:middle line:10%
And it cuts us off
from spirit and choice.

00:08:49.660 --> 00:08:55.210 align:middle line:84%
And it encourages separation,
which fuels ego and greed.

00:08:55.210 --> 00:08:58.900 align:middle line:84%
We don't need to look far to
